    "headerDoc": "STEP 887 — Beal Conjecture: Lean 4 Small-Exponent Formalization\n  ================================================================\n\n  Beal's conjecture (Andrew Beal, 1993):\n    For positive integers x, y, z and exponents a, b, c ≥ 3,\n    if x^a + y^b = z^c, then gcd(x, y, z) > 1.\n\n  Equivalently: x^a + y^b = z^c with gcd(x, y, z) = 1 forces\n  min(a, b, c) ≤ 2.\n\n  Status:\n    - OPEN in full generality.\n    - Fermat's Last Theorem (Wiles 1994) ⟹ Beal for a = b = c ≥ 3.\n    - Verified computationally for z^c ≤ 10^{20} with all exponents ≥ 3.\n    - $1,000,000 prize offered by Beal (now held by AMS"
